

Clone remote repository:                    git clone <string-from-github>


Add file contents to INDEX:                 git add <file>
Remove files from working tree and INDEX:   git rm <file>
Move or rename file or directory:           git mv <source> <destination>
Record change to local repository:          git commit -m <commit-message>


Fetch from remote repository:               git pull
Update remote repository:                   git push


View changes made to working tree:          git diff
View status:                                git status


Get help on git:                            git --help
Get help on git subcommand:                 git <command> --help


Configuration:
  git config --global user.name   <name>
  git config --global user.email  <email-address>
  git config --global core.editor <editor-command>


Documentation:
  https://git-scm.com/docs
  https://git-scm.com/book


Web pages listing resources:
  https://help.github.com/articles/good-resources-for-learning-git-and-github/
  https://www.atlassian.com/git/tutorials/
